metadata.name: Constellation Of Happiness #93
metadata.description:
Constellation Of Happiness is a collaborative art project between NFT artists Kato Trofimova and Andrew Erickson.

Feeling happy is tough this year but it'll be much easier when you get your own constellation of happiness! Using expressionistic code art, Constellation Of Happiness channels the purest festive emotions a person can experience, for example, when tasting champagne bubbles or seeing and touching confetti. All these are turned into beautiful constellations of happiness using the aesthetics of star maps and carefully brought to your NFT collection.

2022

Kato Trofimova (Latvia) is an illustrator, visual artist, and creative director known for her love of minimalistic shapes and bright palettes. In her art, Kato questions boundaries between styles and stays optimistic no matter what.

Andrew Erickson (Switzerland) is a generative artist experimenting with various abstract styles. Be it delicate monochromatic line art or colorful gradient minimalism, Andrew is very good at coding any kind of digital beauty.

Hit 'p' in live mode to save a 9922 × 14032px PNG (for printing up to A0)
Hit 's' in live mode to save a plottable SVG

10% of proceeds go to support Processing.org

License: CC BY-NC-SA-4.0

metadata.name: Aftershock #48
metadata.description:
Turkey was hit by two devastating earthquakes at 6/02/2023 effecting multiple cities.

Aftershock is created to help and support people in earthquake region. 100% of the revenue from primary sales will be send to non governmental organization AHBAP after it's converted to ethereum. All donation will sent from atimtay.eth and will be shared publicly from my twitter account


Artwork info:

Aftershock is based on "Metropolix IX' algorithm. In Metropolis the parameter space was constrained and the cells were painted in a fashion which would create city silhouettes. In Aftershock i removed the constraints and changed the all rulesets and palettes which would give us chaos maybe you can call it a collapsed city.


Features:

6 color palettes and 1 monochrome 
3 subdivison levels 2,3,4 
2 aspect ratios 
10 divison styles 
and some other hidden randomized parameters which doesn't appear on the features but effecting overall outcome

Press 1 to 8 to export PNG at increasing resolution

Murat Atimtay 2023 www.atimtay.xyz

metadata.name: Badgirs City #219
metadata.description:
"I used to live in a small city placed at the center of Iran's plateau with the warmest summer days in the country part; spending most of my childhood with my sweet grandma at her old house. She was always keeping her eyes on me not to get heat stroke at noon playing in the yard when the sun was at its peak glowing furiously. Sundays at noon were my favorite, I used to call them “Ice cream” noons sitting beside the nicest person you could imagine and enjoying a delightful ice cream. You won't know how lovely it was to have an ice cream relaxing under the most enjoyable cold breeze of the tallest windcatcher in the city at her house. "



The Badgirs city is the first collaboration between Fleep and IceRain on Fxhash. The concept was established first with the design of a school with a feeling of safe and nostalgia reminding us of the good memories of our childhood as the grandma’s house and the windcatcher for Fleep.
A windcatcher (Badgir) is an Iranian traditional architectural element in the form of a small tower built on the roof of houses in warm locations to create passive cooling. The collection of Badgirs city is a modern recreational development of those traditional windcatchers designed by Fleep and icerain and exquisitely translated into code by Icerain.

Controls:
[1] Set the resolution to Medium Resolution
[2] Set the resolution to High Resolution

metadata.name: Nullteilung #19
metadata.description:
Nullteilung is another exercise in suprematism and composition. Born from a series of exercises in subdevision and tesselation, it seeks to connect with the user through the creation of a sense of order and balance in the composition.

The term "Nullteilung" a German word that can be translated to "zero division" which is suggesative of the order and disorder paramount in the piece, working toward a goal of emotional and programmatic purity.

metadata.name: Archiplex — Monochrome #78
metadata.description:
Archiplex Monochrome is a long form generative project, building on the short form Archiplex series. The Archiplex Monochrome algorithm is inspired by Brutalist architecture and design, where expressive forms emerge from the use of textures, materials and structures.

Archiplex Monochrome expands on these Brutalist design elements by floating the central structure of each piece and adding random light sources, introducing unpredictability and elevation to a traditionally structured and grounded art form.

"In this series my subject is the structure: formed yet formless, gravity-bound yet weightless, reflective yet light emitting, unmovable yet malleable."

metadata.name: Symbolic Separations #10
metadata.description:
Is this a metaphor for the unstable process of division? Or colours and shapes morphing and inverting along imaginary, fluxing and blurred boundaries?

At least we know it's two passes through two different GLSL shaders, where waves are blurred, turbulence accumulated, and lines drawn to flip colors.

## Controls

Press [spacebar] to toggle play/pause.

When paused, press the keys [1] through [4] to change the resolution.

[1] - 2400px x 2400px

[2] - 3600px x 3600px

[3] - 4800px x 4800px

[4] - 5400px x 5400px

Then (also only when paused) press [p] to create a hi-res PNG.

metadata.name: The Gap #19
metadata.description:
The Gap is an impressive generative art collection that showcases nature in its purest and most elemental form. At the center of the piece is a break between two walls of ice.
 The break appears to have been created by relentless ice pressure, and its shape and size are a result of the complex interaction between water, ice, and underlying geology.
But what truly captures the viewer's attention are the brilliant colors surrounding the break. The sky is depicted in a warm, brilliant color, while the break is depicted in a cold, brilliant color. These flat, saturated colors create a striking contrast that makes the break stand out in the landscape. Together, these colors create a vibrant and evocative atmosphere that invites viewers to dive into the landscape and explore its details.
In summary, The Gap is a unique work that combines technology and nature to create a stunning and impactful visual experience. With its contrast of warm and cold, brilliant flat colors, this work is a statement about the strength and simplicity of nature, and a call to action to protect our planet.

metadata.name: Geode #29
metadata.description:
A single seed shape is chosen from 13, and placed onto the plane. At every step, a copy of this seed is laid edge-to-edge adjacent to an existing shape, without causing any overlaps. This copy is colored based on the edge it shares with the existing shape. The process continues until the animation completes.

New shapes are placed closest to a moving target. In some mints, this target is slow moving, causing new shapes to expand radially from the seed. In other mints, this target races around, causing new shapes to chase it. 

Each of the 13 shapes forms different patterns under different circumstances. Not all patterns will be explored.

Controls:
  - SPACE: Pause/unpause the animation.
  - ENTER: Skip the animation.
  - R: Restart the animation.

URL Params:
  - "preview=1": Skip the animation.
  - "flex=1": Adapt the boundaries to the size of the window.
  - “slow=1”: Draw only one shape per frame.
